The Nigeria Police Force has released human rights activist, Omoyele Sowore. The police had on Thursday illegally arrested Sowore over a frivolous petition by a former member of the House of Representatives, Ned Nwoko. The author, Omoyele Sowore “Released from Nigeria Police Force idiotic arrest and detention. They claimed I defamed a criminal, Ned Nwoko! Useless people. ‪#RevolutionNow‬ ‪#WeCantContinueLikeThis,” the activist posted on Twitter after his release.‬  Released from Nigeria Police Force idiotic arrest and detention. They claimed I defamed a criminal, Ned Nwoko! Useless people. #RevolutionNow #WeCantContinueLikeThis pic.twitter.com/2uaxqrUgkz  A team of armed policemen who laid siege to the entrance of the Court of Appeal had earlier arrested Sowore. See Also






